--- !u!114 &1998444242
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1998444241}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f73ac8e5c01baa44b95c4b0522050928, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  gameSceneName: Gamemode
  tutorialPanel: {fileID: 1962228076}
  tutorialText: {fileID: 1264973043}
  StoryskipButton: {fileID: 1053418768}
  TutorialskipButton: {fileID: 1471815870}
  typingSpeed: 0.03
  storySlides:
  - "The Boy\n\nA small town slept quietly under the night sky.\n\nAmong its people
    lived a boy who could not walk.\nA wheelchair carried him wherever he wished
    to go.\n\nBut even though his legs were weak\u2026\nhis dreams were stronger
    than anyone else's.\n\nPress \"SPACE\" to Continue"
  - "His Wish\n\nEvery night he looked at the stars and wondered:\n\n\"If I had just
    one miracle\u2026 what would I wish for?\"\n\nTo run?\nTo climb mountains?\nOr
    simply to walk like everyone else.\n\nPress \"SPACE\" to Continue"
  - 'The Dream


    One night, something strange happened.


    He dreamed of an
    ancient temple hidden beyond the world he knew.


    A temple whispered about
    only in legends.


    They say the temple grants one wish to those who prove
    themselves worthy.


    Press "SPACE" to Continue'
  - 'The Challenge


    But the temple is not easily reached.


    At its gates
    lie seven riddles. Easch riddle is based on 7 Sins[Pride, Greed, Lust, Envy,
    Gluttony, Wrath, and Sloth]


    Each riddle tests wisdom, courage, and perception.


    Only
    those who solve all seven can reach the sacred chamber.


    Press "SPACE" to
    Continue'
  - "The Power of the Mind\n\nThe boy was brilliant, fascinated by technology and
    physics.\nSince he could not run or jump like others, he built machines to overcome
    his limits\u2014devices to bend gravity, pass through walls, turn invisible,
    and a teleporting blade to cross space.\nIf the temple truly existed, he would
    face its riddles not as a helpless boy, but as the creator of impossible machines..\n\nPress
    \"SPACE\" to Continue"
  - "The Journey Begins\n\nHe gripped the wheels of his chair and looked forward.\nAnd
    maybe\u2026\n\nThis journey will change his fate forever.\n\nPress \"SPACE\"
    to Continue"
  tutorialSteps:
  - "Press \"Left Arrow\" To Throw Knife \n \nPress \"Left Arrow\" to Continue"
  - 'Press "Left Arrow" again to teleport at the position of the Knife


    Press
    "Left Arrow" to Continue'
  - 'Press "UP Arrow"  to Change Gravity


    Press "UP Arrow"  to Continue'
  - 'Press "Right Arrow"  to Active Invisibility


    Press "Right Arrow" to Continue'
  - 'Press "Down Arrow"  to Active  Pass-Through


    Press "Down Arrow" to Continue'
  - "Press \"Space\"  to get back Normal \n\nPress \"Space\" to Continue"
  - 'Press "A or D"  to Move


    Press "A or D" to Continue'
